Class AtomContainer

java.lang.Object
  org.openscience.cdk.ChemObject
      org.openscience.cdk.AtomContainer
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, IAtomContainer, IChemObject, IChemObjectListener
Direct Known Subclasses:
ChargeGroup, Crystal, DebugAtomContainer, Molecule, Monomer, NNAtomContainer, QueryAtomContainer, Residue, Ring, Strand
public class AtomContainer
extends ChemObject
implements IAtomContainer, IChemObjectListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

Base class for all chemical objects that maintain a list of Atoms and ElectronContainers.

Looping over all Bonds in the AtomContainer is typically done like: 

 Iterator iter = atomContainer.bonds();
 while (iter.hasNext()) {
   IBond aBond = (IBond) iter.next();
 }

Parameters:

seCount - Number of single electrons to be in this container
